					<head>Esther scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>10 membranes, 40 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>100/150</height>
										<width>3220</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>10 membranes, with ivory roller and silk green wrapping with threads.  </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Creases. </p>
									<p>A few usage stains.  </p>
									<p>Dirt along edges and slight tidemark near outer end. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="40" ruledLines="13" writtenLines="13">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of membranes distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ and ס, and one on בדהחיק. The letter ח arched sometimes, and occasionally בהםסרת at the end of a line. </p>
									<p>The letter ע flourished in the last word of the Megillah. </p>
									<p>No majuscular or minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 6 lines. </p>
									<p>Ivory roller (150mm high). </p>
									<p>The first and part of the second membrane lined with green silk. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
